article.headline: Cent. Michigan 79, Cal St.-Fullerton 76
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Nate Minnoy had 19 points and five rebounds off the bench for Central Michigan as the Chippewas defeated Cal-State Fullerton 79-76 Saturday night. Josh Akognon missed a 3-pointer as the buzzer sounded which could have sent the game to overtime for the Titans (4-2). The game featured seven lead changes and 10 ties before Central Michigan pulled away for its third straight victory after starting the season 0-5. The Chippewas took a 64-63 lead with 6:32 to play after Giordan Watson made two free throws. Central never trailed afterward but never led by more than six points. The Chippewas missed six free throws in the final 24 seconds that would have extended their 79-76 lead. But the Titans missed on two 3-point attempts and had a turnover on their final three possessions. Watson finished with 18 points for Central, while Jeremy Allen added 17 and Marko Spica 10. Scott Cutley had 21 points and 11 rebounds for Fullerton, while Frank Robinson had 15 points and 10 rebounds. Junior Russell had 16 points.
